title: For Sale:  MAD flip up rear sight $50 (lists for over $100)
postcontent:
The GG&G MAD (Multiple Aperture Device) BUIS (Back Up Iron Sight) was originally developed to fulfill a request from Naval Surface Warfare for a back up iron sight that provided both a large and small aperture on the same plane and would thus be zeroed to the same point of impact. The MAD has four apertures, two of each size (so that rotating the aperture in either direction will bring the next size into view). The small aperture diameter is 0.073-inch and the large aperture is 0.199-inch in diameter. It uses the standard Colt-style windage knob and windage screw. One click of the windage knob provides approximately 0.48 MOA change when mounted on the M16A2E4 rifle and about 0.65 MOA on the M4 carbine.

$50, lists for $129.99 on Brownell's
If interested text me at REDACTED

title: For Sale/Trade:  American Derringer 6" Stainless Over/Under .45lc/.410 Pistol - Texas Commemorative
postcontent:
In the badlands and wild frontiers of the Republic of Texas, rangers and ranchers helped to establish what was to become 150 years of freedom for a great state. This Texas Commemorative Derringer preserves the heroism and romance that make up the history of the Lone Star State.

This pistol is a stainless steel over/under American Derringer. Each barrel is chambered in .45lc (45 Long Colt) and will accept a .410 shell. Being a double-barrel, load one in the top and the other in the bottom and be prepared for anything. It is rifled and has the long 6" barrel, so accuracy isn't terrible, so I wouldn't enter a marksmanship competition with it. But for taking care of snakes or those who are trying to harm you, it's well at home. 

This one has aftermarket larger grips, which means that the recoil isn't all absorbed by the knuckle of your middle finger like with the factory grips. These wood grips are nice and smooth and comfy. 

Also included is a holster and ammo holder that were not designed for the derringer, but make for a nice way to transport the pistol and a selection of ammunition. Included are a few .45lc rounds, some .410 shotshells, and even some .410 PDX rounds. 

American Derringer is well known for making quality guns. This one is no exception. It is fully stainless with a polished finish. This one, like all American Derringers has a hammer-block safety, so you can carry it with a round in each cylinder. Each time you cock it, the mechanism switches between barrels so there is no need to manually flip a lever to take a second shot, unlike some lesser derringers. 

$425 near Fairfax. I'm also open to trades. No Glocks please. Plus or minus cash offers are also ok.
